description.p:
The method of forming the tool 200 of the present invention generally includes the following steps:


1. providing a generally cylindrical tool blank (not shown);


2. grinding the primary flute 210 at the low helix angle  BETA  into the body portion 206;


3. grinding the second primary flute 212 at the low helix angle  BETA  into the body portion 206;


4. grinding the first secondary flute 220 at the high helix angle  THETA  into the body portion 206;


5. grinding the second secondary flute 222 at the high helix angle  THETA  into the body portion 206;


6. grinding the third secondary flute 224 at the high helix angle  THETA  into the body portion 206;


7. grinding the fourth secondary flute 226 at the high helix angle  THETA  into the body portion 206;


8. grinding continuous cutting reliefs 236 on each of the compound helical cutting surfaces 228 by following the low helix angle  BETA  until the intersection point 240 and following the high helix angle  THETA  thereafter;


9. grinding continuous clearance reliefs 238 on each of the compound helical cutting surfaces 228 by following the low helix angle  BETA  until the intersection point 240 and following the high helix angle  THETA  thereafter;


10. grinding reliefs and clearances at the point 204 to form the cutting edges 214-216.
